WEBVTT

00:02.700 --> 00:03.100
Previously

00:03.100 --> 00:04.166
Previously
on "Below Deck Med"...

00:10.567 --> 00:13.300
- Dude, we both kissed Malia
last night.

00:13.333 --> 00:15.033
- Let's just take it
day by day, right?

00:15.066 --> 00:17.166
- Primary guests
Ken and Amber

00:17.166 --> 00:18.567
are regular charter clients.

00:18.567 --> 00:20.133
- I may need some wine.
[laughter]

00:20.166 --> 00:23.433
- Is that Kenny again?
[laughter]

00:23.433 --> 00:25.300
- The Krka waterfalls

00:25.300 --> 00:27.133
are some of the most beautiful
in Europe.

00:27.166 --> 00:28.700
They don't allow yachts
up the river,

00:28.734 --> 00:30.433
so we need to take a ferry.

00:30.467 --> 00:32.433
So I'm gonna send you
to these waterfalls.

00:32.433 --> 00:34.433
- Four of the guests
have written, "No onions."

00:34.433 --> 00:37.166
I'm having trouble with
this whole "no onion" thing.

00:38.734 --> 00:40.600
- Can we get another one
with no onions?

00:40.600 --> 00:43.200
- Got you,
you little slut.

00:43.200 --> 00:46.200
- I think that we can send
another stew.

00:46.233 --> 00:48.000
- She doesn't need
to be coming to me

00:48.033 --> 00:49.734
and telling me where
I should send my stews.

00:49.767 --> 00:53.200
Adam, I really can't look after,
like, the inside and your food.

00:53.200 --> 00:54.467
- Most can.

00:54.467 --> 00:55.600
- Well, I guess
I'm a f---ing bad

00:55.600 --> 00:57.266
chief stew, then, all right?

00:57.300 --> 00:59.200
- Maybe Bugsy should be
the chief stew.

00:59.200 --> 01:00.667
- Unbelievable.

01:02.300 --> 01:04.166
[horn blares]

01:04.200 --> 01:07.166
[upbeat music]

01:07.200 --> 01:14.166
♪ ♪

01:18.200 --> 01:20.500
- Attention, all crew.

01:20.500 --> 01:22.633
The ferry to Krka
will be delayed.

01:22.667 --> 01:24.500
The departure time
is now 1:30.

01:24.500 --> 01:26.033
- I've just got spoiling food

01:26.066 --> 01:28.233
in a hot Croatian barge.

01:28.266 --> 01:30.767
So the food needed to be ready
40 minutes ago?

01:31.000 --> 01:32.500
- Yeah, the ferry was
supposed to leave at 12:30.

01:32.500 --> 01:34.200
- Hope they don't get sick.

01:34.233 --> 01:35.633
- Are those real goggle--
like, do they--

01:35.633 --> 01:37.367
[people talking and laughing]

01:37.400 --> 01:38.767
- Not much I can do
about that, Adam.

01:39.000 --> 01:40.233
You know, they changed things.

01:40.233 --> 01:41.633
- Well, I could have
kept it cold

01:41.633 --> 01:43.367
for the last 40 minutes,
had you told me.

01:43.400 --> 01:45.233
Hannah's making my job
so difficult right now.

01:45.233 --> 01:46.300
It's like she's continuing

01:46.333 --> 01:48.100
this looming ability

01:48.100 --> 01:50.367
to f--- with me and my timing.

01:50.400 --> 01:52.500
- Adam, I really can't
look after the inside

01:52.500 --> 01:55.333
and your food, so you're welcome
to take the initiative directly.

01:55.367 --> 01:56.633
- It's your job
to just let me know that.

01:56.667 --> 01:58.500
- Yeah, but I don't know.

01:58.500 --> 02:01.066
You go and communicate,
'cause I can't do both.

02:01.100 --> 02:02.333
- Most can.

02:02.367 --> 02:03.533
- Well, I guess
I'm a f---king bad

02:03.533 --> 02:05.233
chief stew, then,
all right?

02:05.266 --> 02:07.133
- Maybe Bugsy should be
the chief stew.

02:07.166 --> 02:10.333
That's generally who gets
all the sh-- done anyway.

02:10.367 --> 02:12.133
[dramatic music]

02:12.166 --> 02:15.000
- No one ever speaks to me
like that.

02:15.000 --> 02:16.133
Ever.

02:16.133 --> 02:17.533
Maybe we should get a chef

02:17.533 --> 02:19.667
that can read
f---ing preference sheets.

02:19.700 --> 02:22.333
- The onion thing
was kind of a fiasco.

02:22.367 --> 02:24.133
Bugsy's killing it, though.

02:24.133 --> 02:26.667
- This is a really low blow
from Adam.

02:26.700 --> 02:29.000
I have to work closely
with the both of them,

02:29.000 --> 02:30.767
and I don't want to be caught

02:31.000 --> 02:32.066
in any of their issues.

02:34.433 --> 02:35.533
- Let's do this, guys.

02:35.567 --> 02:36.667
We got to be off the boat.

02:36.700 --> 02:38.133
- Ready?
- We're ready!

02:38.133 --> 02:39.266
- Head-butt a tree
or two, hey?

02:39.300 --> 02:40.400
- [laughs]
- Whoo!

02:40.433 --> 02:42.400
- Let's head on out, guys.

02:42.400 --> 02:44.567
- Anywhere you'd like.
- Yay!

02:44.600 --> 02:46.567
- Let's pop the bottles.

02:46.567 --> 02:48.166
- Yes!
- Here you are.

02:48.166 --> 02:50.266
- Hey, chasing waterfalls.

02:50.300 --> 02:51.667
- Day two.

02:56.066 --> 02:57.567
- That's some bullsh--.

02:57.567 --> 03:00.433
For Adam to diminish my rank

03:00.467 --> 03:02.300
in front
of my second stewardess,

03:02.333 --> 03:03.700
I don't need that.

03:03.734 --> 03:05.700
I have three stripes,
and she has two.

03:05.700 --> 03:09.533
And as a chef,
you should respect that.

03:09.567 --> 03:12.033
[sighs]

03:12.033 --> 03:13.700
[upbeat music]

03:13.734 --> 03:15.667
- Hey, is there any way
we can jump off this bridge?

03:15.700 --> 03:17.567
[laughter]

03:17.567 --> 03:20.133
- I'll just keep your glass
full; how about that?

03:20.166 --> 03:21.567
- Oh, no.

03:21.567 --> 03:23.567
White deck shorts down.

03:23.567 --> 03:26.333
- Oh, that was an easy one.
Came right out.

03:26.333 --> 03:29.300
- Finally, I got Malia
right by my side,

03:29.333 --> 03:31.066
and I've got this kind of--

03:31.100 --> 03:34.033
this burning feeling in me,
and I want to pursue it.

03:34.066 --> 03:35.600
- I think we can start going.

03:35.600 --> 03:37.333
- Wes?
- Yeah.

03:37.333 --> 03:38.667
- Do you want to come
for a walk with me?

03:38.700 --> 03:40.200
- All right.
- Let's go.

03:40.233 --> 03:41.600
- Sweet.

03:41.600 --> 03:42.734
- So everybody can start
walking with me.

03:42.734 --> 03:44.133
- Let's run.

03:44.166 --> 03:46.734
- Oh, my gosh.

03:46.734 --> 03:49.200
[gasps]
Look at that!

03:49.233 --> 03:52.600
- The Krka waterfalls
are absolutely breathtaking.

03:52.600 --> 03:55.600
It's not something you'll see
in Italy or France.

03:55.600 --> 03:57.734
It's out of a fairy tale,
really.

03:57.734 --> 03:59.467
- It's beautiful.

03:59.500 --> 04:01.200
- We're gonna make the buffet
on the table.

04:01.200 --> 04:03.066
Right there in the middle.

04:03.066 --> 04:05.467
- Somebody needs to baptize
my ass in this water.

04:05.467 --> 04:07.333
- Hey, I'm an ordained guy.

04:07.367 --> 04:08.500
- Put it on the corner here,
Lauren,

04:08.533 --> 04:10.233
so it's, like, over this branch.

04:10.233 --> 04:11.734
- I'm so glad you're here.

04:11.767 --> 04:13.500
Hannah wanted to send me
to do this by myself.

04:13.500 --> 04:14.500
- Yeah.

04:14.500 --> 04:16.367
♪ ♪

04:16.367 --> 04:17.500
- Trying to find
a bottle of Jaeger.

04:17.500 --> 04:19.367
- Mm-hmm.

04:19.367 --> 04:21.233
- Ten bottles of Tito's,
ten bottles of Grey Goose,

04:21.233 --> 04:23.233
ten bottles of cab sav.

04:23.266 --> 04:25.066
This was it, wasn't it?
- Hi.

04:25.100 --> 04:26.367
- To great decisions.

04:26.367 --> 04:28.100
- Another life experience
together.

04:28.100 --> 04:30.600
- Amazing.
- Looks good, doesn't it?

04:30.633 --> 04:32.767
- This is just some chicken
that we marinated and grilled,

04:33.000 --> 04:34.233
some hummus over here.

04:34.233 --> 04:35.500
- This looks so good.

04:35.500 --> 04:37.633
- Are there any onions
in this?

04:37.633 --> 04:38.767
- Not a one.

04:38.767 --> 04:40.600
I've met Kennys before

04:40.633 --> 04:42.100
on these charters.

04:42.100 --> 04:43.433
Kennys are my rival.

04:43.467 --> 04:45.500
Kennys ruin my job.

04:45.500 --> 04:48.100
- The primary said there's
chunks of onion in this,

04:48.133 --> 04:49.667
so he doesn't want
to eat it.

04:49.667 --> 04:51.533
- No, that's not
how it works, Kenny.

04:51.567 --> 04:53.133
You need to be appreciative.

04:53.166 --> 04:54.734
- What we got here?
Is that hummus?

04:56.533 --> 04:58.266
- Last night,
the head charter guest

04:58.300 --> 05:00.000
was like, "Just no onion."

05:00.000 --> 05:02.000
And so what does Adam put
in the sauce? Onions.

05:02.000 --> 05:04.633
The main charter guest, Kenny,
sent the meal back,

05:04.667 --> 05:06.133
and he was like,
"Okay, Hannah,

05:06.166 --> 05:08.133
yeah, I see
what you're doing."

05:08.166 --> 05:09.667
And I was like, "Adam, it's not
me sending the food back."

05:09.700 --> 05:11.000
- Yeah.
- You know?

05:11.000 --> 05:12.133
"Can you not have attitude?"

05:12.166 --> 05:13.467
And he goes,
"You know what?

05:13.500 --> 05:15.000
"Bugsy's actually doing
a great job.

05:15.000 --> 05:16.000
I think she should be
chief stew."

05:16.000 --> 05:17.533
- Jeez.

05:17.567 --> 05:19.100
So he kind of decided
to snap a bit.

05:19.133 --> 05:20.667
- Yeah.

05:20.667 --> 05:22.266
- People are gonna come
out of their shells

05:22.266 --> 05:24.133
and show you
who they really are,

05:24.166 --> 05:25.467
and Adam, he's turning out
to be an ogre on the inside.

05:25.500 --> 05:27.133
- I know why
he's getting angry.

05:27.133 --> 05:28.633
It's because he's f---ing up.
- Yeah.

05:28.667 --> 05:30.166
- And, like,
at the end of the day,

05:30.200 --> 05:32.500
our tip relies a lot
on service and food.

05:32.533 --> 05:34.166
- Yeah, 100%.

05:34.166 --> 05:36.166
- Oh, my gosh, it is good.

05:36.166 --> 05:38.333
- I think this is couscous.
- What's that?

05:42.300 --> 05:43.700
- Delicious.

05:43.700 --> 05:44.700
- All in all,
we did pretty good.

05:44.700 --> 05:47.166
- F---ing winner.

05:48.700 --> 05:50.700
- Mm-hmm.

05:51.700 --> 05:53.233
- Yeah.

05:55.333 --> 05:57.033
- What about on your nipple
with the sun around it?

05:57.066 --> 05:58.700
[laughter]

05:58.700 --> 06:00.667
- You guys sneaking off
and get in the bushes?

06:03.300 --> 06:05.667
- He just throws himself
on it, you know?

06:05.700 --> 06:07.033
- Were you really into her?
- Malia?

06:07.066 --> 06:08.166
- Yeah.
- No, yeah.

06:08.166 --> 06:09.567
I think she's awesome.

06:09.600 --> 06:11.433
But I'm not the guy
that grabs a girl

06:11.433 --> 06:13.066
and just makes out
with them

06:13.100 --> 06:14.600
or "Oh, come here;
let's go do this."

06:14.600 --> 06:16.066
You know, that's not me.

06:16.066 --> 06:17.467
Yeah, I have a crush on Malia.

06:17.467 --> 06:18.600
But it's like
I never get a chance

06:18.633 --> 06:20.467
to have her get to know me,

06:20.500 --> 06:23.333
because Wes is always scheduling
them working together.

06:23.333 --> 06:25.166
And then when I'm working,

06:25.200 --> 06:27.066
Adam's pulling her off
to go on a walk

06:27.066 --> 06:28.066
to the waterfalls.

06:28.066 --> 06:29.333
- You're going swimming?

06:29.367 --> 06:30.567
- You're going swimming
with me.

06:30.600 --> 06:32.066
- I don't have
swimming stuff on.

06:32.100 --> 06:33.700
- Here comes Bobby in ten years.

06:33.734 --> 06:35.433
- That's right;
just take your clothes off.

06:35.467 --> 06:37.333
- Shot before you swim.

06:37.367 --> 06:39.066
- Oh, they're going to town.

06:39.066 --> 06:40.200
- Oh, yeah.

06:40.200 --> 06:41.567
- That's more like it.

06:41.600 --> 06:43.200
Actually get to see something.

06:43.200 --> 06:44.600
- Yeah, this is cool.

06:44.600 --> 06:46.266
- It's nice
to finally get away.

06:46.300 --> 06:48.333
I was starting to think
it wasn't gonna happen.

06:48.333 --> 06:49.734
Turn around.

06:51.200 --> 06:52.734
Perfect.

06:52.734 --> 06:55.367
[upbeat music]

06:55.400 --> 06:57.200
- We're gonna go get
in the water.

06:57.233 --> 06:59.233
- You enjoying Croatia
so far?

06:59.266 --> 07:01.367
- Mm-hmm.
- You like your crew?

07:01.367 --> 07:03.367
- Yes, I do.

07:03.400 --> 07:04.767
Wes is very smart.

07:04.767 --> 07:07.233
He's a good teacher.

07:07.233 --> 07:08.633
I like being on the outside.

07:08.667 --> 07:10.500
- I like you being
on the outside.

07:10.500 --> 07:12.100
I'd probably be yelling at you

07:12.100 --> 07:13.500
like I yell at Hannah
every day.

07:13.533 --> 07:15.100
What's next
after you get out of here?

07:15.100 --> 07:16.500
- I've never been to Greece.

07:16.533 --> 07:18.200
I really want to go.

07:18.233 --> 07:19.467
- I've never been
to Greece either.

07:19.500 --> 07:20.767
I think that'd be
pretty cool.

07:21.000 --> 07:22.467
Where do you want to go?
- All over.

07:22.500 --> 07:24.233
- Could you see yourself,
you know,

07:24.266 --> 07:25.767
maybe doing this again
in the future

07:25.767 --> 07:26.767
on a different boat?

07:27.000 --> 07:28.200
- Yeah, definitely.

07:28.233 --> 07:29.500
- Yeah?
- Mm-hmm.

07:29.533 --> 07:30.633
- Maybe on the West Coast?

07:30.633 --> 07:33.367
- Maybe.

07:33.367 --> 07:35.700
- Whoo!
- [laughs]

07:37.667 --> 07:40.133
- They can get lost
for all I care.

07:40.166 --> 07:42.133
- I'm glad I finally got
to spend some time with you.

07:42.133 --> 07:43.633
- Yeah.

07:50.667 --> 07:52.400
- Part of me is still thinking

07:52.400 --> 07:54.767
Wes didn't get
this opportunity.

07:55.000 --> 07:57.000
He's back on the boat.
And it's hard.

07:57.033 --> 08:00.233
I'm honestly getting to know
two very different guys,

08:00.266 --> 08:03.467
and there's something attractive
about each of them.

08:06.400 --> 08:13.400
♪ ♪

08:14.533 --> 08:16.400
- How was it?

08:16.400 --> 08:18.300
- Oh, it was so good.
- It was good?

08:18.300 --> 08:20.033
- How'd it go?
- Good to go.

08:20.033 --> 08:22.100
- Better start packing up.

08:22.133 --> 08:23.567
- Let's go garbage in here.

08:23.567 --> 08:25.033
Put the utensils in there.

08:25.066 --> 08:27.000
- Let's go.

08:27.033 --> 08:29.433
[people cheering]

08:29.433 --> 08:32.300
- Go, Bobby, go!

08:32.300 --> 08:34.700
- To the boat.

08:34.700 --> 08:37.433
♪ ♪

08:37.467 --> 08:39.700
- Guests approaching.
- Copy.

08:39.734 --> 08:42.000
[people yelling and whooping]

08:42.033 --> 08:44.166
- Welcome back, everyone.
- Hello!

08:44.166 --> 08:46.433
- The Jacuzzi's ready to go.
- Awesome.

08:46.433 --> 08:48.700
- What a beautiful day.
- Thank you so much.

08:48.700 --> 08:50.567
- That's good.
- Oh, that was good.

08:50.567 --> 08:52.166
- Oh, we're gonna need
another one of those.

08:52.166 --> 08:54.033
- There's no waters
by the bar.

08:54.033 --> 08:56.300
- Okay, Lau, can you send some
through to the bar?

08:56.300 --> 08:58.033
- Thank you.

08:58.033 --> 08:59.300
- Wes, I thought you were
gonna clean the windows

08:59.333 --> 09:01.066
when we were gone.

09:01.100 --> 09:03.066
- Oh, I decided to take
a nap instead, you know?

09:03.066 --> 09:05.600
- Oh, yes.
- Oh, it's so warm.

09:05.633 --> 09:06.734
♪ ♪

09:06.767 --> 09:09.633
- I got a spritz and martinis.

09:11.734 --> 09:14.066
- I think, like last time,
8:30-ish, 9:00.

09:14.100 --> 09:15.200
- Uh-huh.

09:15.233 --> 09:17.467
♪ ♪

09:17.467 --> 09:19.066
- Just so you know,

09:19.066 --> 09:20.467
the primary's wife
has asked me about dinner.

09:20.467 --> 09:22.066
I said it's probably
between 8:30 and 9:00.

09:22.100 --> 09:23.300
- I appreciate the update.
Thank you.

09:23.333 --> 09:25.200
Oh, Amber just dislikes mussels.

09:25.233 --> 09:27.667
- You should just make
everything what they dislike.

09:27.700 --> 09:30.333
- That's pretty much
where I'm at at this point.

09:30.367 --> 09:32.300
- No, I was joking.
That was a joke.

09:32.333 --> 09:34.200
- Kenny, he rubbed me
the wrong way

09:34.200 --> 09:37.600
the moment he pulled out
this whole onion pizzazz.

09:37.633 --> 09:39.600
People that I cook for
hire me

09:39.600 --> 09:41.600
because they like my food,

09:41.633 --> 09:44.100
and this redneck's gonna try
and pull me through the mud?

09:44.133 --> 09:45.233
Sorry, Charlie.

09:45.233 --> 09:47.100
♪ ♪

09:47.133 --> 09:49.600
- I laughed when he said,
"You want a f---in' drink?"

09:49.633 --> 09:52.367
And I said, "Yeah."

09:52.367 --> 09:54.500
- Can't have lentil soup
without some onions in it,

09:54.500 --> 09:57.066
so I'm gonna chuck some onions
in that soup.

10:02.767 --> 10:04.233
- If it was
a different situation...

10:04.266 --> 10:05.567
- Bobby...
- You'd be interested.

10:05.600 --> 10:06.767
- Mm...

10:07.000 --> 10:08.033
- And later...

10:15.367 --> 10:16.367
- Right.

10:20.233 --> 10:20.633
[upbeat electronic music]

10:23.133 --> 10:30.166
♪ ♪

10:33.000 --> 10:34.133
- Adam, Adam, Hannah.

10:34.133 --> 10:35.667
- Yeah, go for Adam.

10:35.667 --> 10:38.000
- Have you got the menu ready
for me?

10:38.000 --> 10:40.266
- Yeah, it's been down here
on the counter for a while.

10:40.266 --> 10:42.000
- I'll come grab it.

10:42.033 --> 10:46.533
♪ ♪

10:46.533 --> 10:49.133
- Adam, I'm just going to go
and round up the guests

10:49.133 --> 10:50.133
and get them seated, okay?

10:50.133 --> 10:52.000
- Okay.

10:52.000 --> 10:54.533
- I'm hoping tonight's meal
goes without a hitch,

10:54.533 --> 10:57.400
and I don't need
to prove myself to anyone.

10:57.400 --> 11:00.400
So, guys, just so you have
a heads-up,

11:00.433 --> 11:03.066
we have something planned
for tomorrow.

11:03.100 --> 11:06.300
We're gonna do a obstacle course
in the morning.

11:06.300 --> 11:07.767
- Is it a competition?

11:08.000 --> 11:09.300
- It's a competition.

11:09.333 --> 11:11.166
We're gonna do crew
versus you guys.

11:11.200 --> 11:14.033
- I love obstacle courses.
- I can't wait, Hannah.

11:14.066 --> 11:16.567
- Now we're gonna go up
for dinner.

11:16.567 --> 11:18.166
- Okay, let's go, folks.

11:18.166 --> 11:20.033
♪ ♪

11:20.066 --> 11:23.700
- [gasps]
Look at the table, you guys!

11:23.734 --> 11:26.133
It's beautiful!

11:26.166 --> 11:28.567
- Wow.
- [sighs]

11:28.567 --> 11:30.300
- Lauren, Lauren, Hannah.

11:30.300 --> 11:32.166
Do you want to pop up
to the pantry

11:32.166 --> 11:33.433
and give me a hand
with service, please?

11:33.433 --> 11:34.734
- Yeah.

11:39.166 --> 11:40.700
- Okay, ready to rock and roll?

11:40.734 --> 11:42.300
- Let me just throw some herbs,
and you can go.

11:42.300 --> 11:44.433
- Okay.
- Got a little smudge.

11:44.433 --> 11:46.233
- Thank you very much.

11:47.734 --> 11:50.200
- This wine is fantastic.

11:50.233 --> 11:53.467
- This is the main course.
- [laughs]

11:53.467 --> 11:56.600
- It's got parsley.

11:56.600 --> 12:00.467
- So tonight to start,
we've got a fresh lentil soup.

12:00.500 --> 12:02.467
- Lentil.
